520days%2520across%2520the%2520U.S.%2Cand%2520opened%2520a%2520political%2520debate.%26amp%3Btext%3DThe%2520president%2520had%2520been%2520discussing%2CBlinken%2527s%2520planned%2520visit%2520to%2520China.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvised%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20shooting%20the%20Chinese%20balloon%20down%20over%20land%2C%20warning%20that%20the%20debris%20could%20harm%20people%20and%20infrastructure.%20The%20delay%20in%20intercepting%20it%20sparked%20domestic%20debate%20and%20blame.%20When%20the%20American%20military%20finally%20shot%20it%20down%2C%20there%20were%20discussions%20of%20the%20deep%20cost-imbalance%20of%20using%20a%20fifth-generation%20fighter%20and%20air-to-air%20missiles%20costing%20around%20%24400%2C000%20each%20to%20bring%20it%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigh-altitude%20spy%20balloons%20are%20not%20a%20new%20capability.%20They've%20been%20around%20since%20the%201950s.%20The%20technology%20is%20relatively%20cheap%20and%20deniable%2C%20easy%20to%20present%20as%20meteorological%20research%20tools%20rather%20than%20surveillance%20assets.%20Amid%20the%20Chinese%20spy%20balloon%20incident%2C%20Beijing%20said%20the%20balloon%20was%20a%20weather%20balloon%20that%20had%20gone%20astray.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBalloons%2C%20though%20now%20notably%20improved%20over%20the%20early%20models%2C%20persist%20because%20of%20their%20altitude%2C%20endurance%2C%20low%20cost%2C%20and%20ambiguity%20of%20purpose.%20The%20balloons%20offer%20options%20outside%20of%20spy%20planes%2C%20like%20the%20American%20U-2%20Dragon%20Lady%2C%20and%20satellites.%20Modern%20spy%20balloons%20are%20a%20mix%20of%20established%20technology%20and%20ongoing%20innovation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENewer%20balloons%20can%20carry%20much%20more%20advanced%20surveillance%20capabilities%2C%20such%20as%20high-resolution%20multispectral%20sensors%2C%20signals%20and%20electronic%20intelligence%20options%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigh-altitude%20spy%20balloons%20can%20cause%20a%20host%20of%20problems%2C%20from