y%20sale%20in%20a%20startup's%20early%20years%20to%20avoid%20a%20massive%20tax%20hit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20those%20profits%20will%20be%2050%25%20tax-free%20after%20three%20years%2C%2075%25%20after%20four%2C%20and%20completely%20tax-free%20after%20five.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVenture%20investors%20and%20startups%20who've%20caught%20on%20to%20the%20changes%2C%20and%20what%20they%20could%20mean%20for%20earlier%20startup%20exits%2C%20are%20buzzing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20the%20previous%20five-year%20exit%20minimum%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20don't%20get%20the%20benefit%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Luke%20Fischer%2C%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20geospatial%20tech%20startup%20SkyFi.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20this%20looks%20like%20a%20forward-leaning%20administration%20that%20understands%20the%20reality%20of%20business%20and%20what%20that%20means%20for%20those%20folks%20to%20deploy%20their%20hard-earned%20capital%2C%20with%20the%20tax-free%20benefit%2C%20back%20into%20their%20own%20company%20or%20into%20a%20new%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220cafffb8-64c9-4cdf-b1b0-06420fc76bf9%5C%22%3EBreaking%20down%20the%20changes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20updates%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fqsbs-qualified-small-business-stock-startups-criteria-taxes-2019-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EQualified%20Small%20Business%20Stock%3C%2Fa%3E%20rules%2C%20or%20QSBS%2C%20expand%20the%20definition%20of%20a%20small%20business%20to%20include%20companies%20with%20less%20than%20%2475%20million%20in%20gross%20assets%2C%20up%20from%20the%20previous%20%2450%20million%20cap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFounders%2C%20investors%2C%20and%20employees%20who%20acquire%20a%20stake%20in%20a%20company%20before%20it%20hits%20%2475%20million%20in%20assets%20can%20now%20cash%20out%20down%20the%20line%20and%20get%20up%20to%20%2415%20million%20in%20profits%20per%20taxpayer%20from%20a%20sale%20of%20the%20startup's%20shares%20tax-free%2C%20or%20up%20to%2010%20times%20their%20initial%20investment%20in%20profits%20tax-free%2C%20whichever%20amount%20is%20greater.%20That's%20up%20from%20a%20previous%20%2410%20million%20profit%20cap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20other%20limitations%20apply.%20Businesses%20that%20primarily%20sell%20services%2C%20like%20hospitals%20and%20law%20firms%2C%20don't%20qualify%20for%20QSBS%20benefits.%20Companies%20must%20also%20be%20registered%20as%20C%20corporations%20to%20qualify.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVenture%20capital%20lawyer%20Chris%20Harvey%20pointed%20out%20that%20plenty%20of%20companies%20that%20last%20raised%20capital%20years%20ago%20and%20saw%20their%20assets%20hit%20%2450%20million%20or%20more%2C%20boxing%20them%20out%20of%20QSBS%20benefits%2C%20may%20now%20be%20eligible%20if%20their%20total%20assets%20don't%20exceed%20%2475%20million.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20expansion%20also%20likely%20brings%20more%20Series%20A-%20and%20B-stage%20startups%20into%20the%20mix%2C%20he%20said.%20The%20average%20sizes%20of%20Series%20A%20and%20B%20funding%20rounds%20have%20decreased%20since%20the%202021%20funding%20boom%2C%20which%20means%20startups%20may%20have%20raised%20less%20money%20overall%20later%20in%20their%20lifecycles%2C%20potentially%20extending%20their%20eligibility%20for%20QSBS%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20at%20a%20company%20in%20that%20category%20and%20you%20have%20options%2C%20you%20might%20have%20previously%20thought%2C%20why%20even%20bother%20exercising%20my%20options.%20Now%20there%20may%20be%20a%20pathway%20for%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Harvey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b5428dfd-2d44-4e30-99cb-e5469ab367b4%5C%22%3EMore%20M%26amp%3BA%20could%20be%20on%20the%20table%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20updated%20provisions'%20biggest%20promise%20could%20be%20the%20potential%20for%20more%2C%20earlier%20M%26amp%3BA.%20%26quot%3BStartups%20can%20now%20actually%20entertain%20an%20acquisition%20offer%20at%20three%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fseed-100-best-early-stage-vc-investors-2025-5%2385.-milad-alucozai%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMilad%20Alucozai%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20cofounder%20and%20general%20partner%20at%20Pamir%20Ventures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20July%20changes%2C%20any%20acquisition%20offers%20that%20a%20small%20business%20received%20before%20the%20five-year%20mark%20had%20a%20huge%20caveat%3A%20they'd%20be%20subject%20to%20massive%20taxes%20on%20any%20profits%20made%20from%20the%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20startup%20M%26amp%3BA%20timelines%20can%20vary%20wildly%2C%20most%20data%20suggests%20that%20startups%20get%20acquired%20on%20average%20between%20the%20five-%20and%20ten-year%20mark.%20However%2C%20Alucozai%20said%20that%20he's%20seeing%20more%20companies%2C%20especially%20AI%20startups%2C%20get%20acquisition%20offers%20earlier%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-scale-ai-15-billion-alexandr-wang-acquihire-ai-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBig%20Tech%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20industries%20scramble%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fin-silicon-valley-it-is-the-summer-of-fomo-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Escoop%20up%20AI%20assets%20and%20talent.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20changes%20could%20also%20make%20secondary%20sales%20more%20attractive.%20While%20secondary%20transactions%20usually%20happen%20later%20in%20a%20startup's%20life%2C%20Menlo%20Ventures%20principal%20Deedy%20Das%20suggested%20that%20the%20new%20provisions%20could%20encourage%20founders%20to%20entertain%20those%20deals%20earlier%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20probably%20will%20increase%20the%20willingness%20of%20early%20employees%20and%20founders%20to%20sell%20in%20three%20to%20five%20years%20after%20their%20equity%20vests%20with%20the%20huge%20tax%20benefit%2C%20so%20we'll%20likely%20see%20more%20secondary%20sales%20for%20good%20companies%20where%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20investor%20demand%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22032089a0-84c4-41ce-b43b-e809968c5d19%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGray%20areas%20and%20brain%20drain%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20will%20overwhelmingly%20benefit%20from%20the%20QSBS%20expansions%2C%20since%20they%20hold%20nearly%2060%25%20of%20all%20qualified%20small%20business%20stock%2C%20according%20to%20Carta%20data%20from%20August%202024.%20Founders%20follow%20behind%2C%20with%2026%25.%20Employees%20hold%20about%2010%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployees%20with%20stock%20options%20aren't%20off%20the%20hook%20on%20taxes%2C%20either%2C%20since%20they%20have%20to%20pay%20to%20convert%20their%20options%20into%20shares%20and%20face%20taxes%20on%20that%20conversion.%20Founders%20and%20investors%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20generally%20own%20company%20stock%20from%20the%20jump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarvey%20said%20more%20changes%20would%20need%20to%20be%20made%20to%20QSBS%20provisions%20for%20the%20tax%20benefits%20to%20apply%20fairly%20to%20employees%2C%20founders%2C%20and%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20pointed%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20clarity%20in%20the%20new%20provisions%20about%20how%20SAFEs%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-founders-safe-notes-amid-funding-gold-rush-from-vc-investors-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esimple%20agreements%20for%20future%20equity%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20would%20be%20handled.%20SAFEs%20are%20commonly%20used%20by%20pre-seed%20and%20seed-stage%20startups%20to%20raise%20capital%20and%20promise%20equity%20to%20an%20investor%20down%20the%20line.%20However%2C%20those%20investors%20would%20likely%20have%20to%20be%20able%20to%20convert%20their%20shares%20to%20equity%20before%20a%20startup%20hit%20%2475%20million%20in%20gross%20assets%2C%20Harvey%20said.%20That%20could%20get%20complicated%2C%20since%20SAFE%20conversions%20usually%20happen%20at%20the%20company's%20next%20fundraise%2C%20adding%20more%20money%20that%20could%20disqualify%20the%20startup%20from%20QSBS%