Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecalling%20an%20experience%20working%20with%20a%20weaving%20cluster%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20used%20to%20have%20our%20meals%20at%20different%20homes%20each%20day.%20However%2C%20one%20particularly%20hot%20summer%20day%2C%20I%20developed%20a%20headache%20and%20lost%20my%20appetite.%20I%20declined%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ealoo%20chole%20puri%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0that%20was%20prepared%20for%20me%20and%20instead%20requested%20the%20same%C2%A0%3Cem%3Echaas%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eroti%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0that%20her%20son%20was%20eating.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3Cem%3EChaas%20roti%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eor%20simply%20buttermilk%20and%20chapati%20is%20often%20made%20during%20the%20summers%20when%20it%20gets%20too%20hot%20to%20cook%20on%20an%20open%20fire%20mud%20stove.%20The%20dish%20is%20simple%2C%20made%20with%20leftover%20dried%20chapati%20bites%20crushed%20into%20a%20bowl%20of%20cold%20buttermilk%20with%20onions%2C%20mint%2C%20green%20chillies%20and%20salt.%20It%20is%20a%20naturally%20cooling%20recipe%20that%20protects%20from%20the%20strong%20gusts%20of%20loo.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20she%20said%20it%20in%20front%20of%20her%20son%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20something%20I%20would%20like%20because%20it%20is%20the%20food%20of%C2%A0%3Cem%3Edehati%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20derogatory%20term%20for%20villagers).%20I%20think%20that%E2%80%99s%20one%20incident%2C%20I%20can%20never%20take%20out%20of%20my%20head%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dipali%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20any%20urban-looking%20person%20asks%20them%20for%20local%20food%2C%20they%E2%80%99ll%20end%20up%20making%C2%A0%3Cem%3Edaal%20bati%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(Lentil%20and%20wheat%20bread%20balls)%2C%20thinking%20that%E2%80%99s%20all%20we%20have%20the%20taste%20for%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20reflects.%20The%20pressure%20to%20conform%20to%20urban%20food%20preferences%20and%20the%20commercialisation%20of%20local%20food%20culture%20was%20evident.%20But%20the%20irony%2C%20as%20Dipali%20found%2C%20was%20that%20these%20people%20were%20sitting%20on%20a%20treasure%20trove%20of%20unique%2C%20locally%20grown%2C%20and%20indigenous%20foods%20%E2%80%94%20foods%20that%20were%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20being%20lost%20forever.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20Dipali%E2%80%99s%20journey%20began%20as%20a%20personal%20quest%20to%20understand%20her%20roots.%20This%20led%20her%20to%20embark%20on%20in-depth%20research%2C%20exploring%20the%20remote%20corners%20of%20Rajasthan.%20She%20meticulously%20documented%20local%20eating%20habits%2C%20indigenous%20ingredients%2C%20their%20seasonal%20availability%2C%20storage%20techniques%2C%20and%20the%20diverse%20recipes%20they%20inspired.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20broadly%20identifies%20nine%20cultural%20zones%20in%20Rajasthan%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20geography%2C%20the%20agricultural%20features%2C%20and%20language.%20Due%20to%20its%20location%2C%20Marwar%2C%20or%20the%20desert%20region%20of%20Rajasthan%2C%20has%20always%20depended%20on%20forged%20ingredients%20instead%20of%20greens.%20Ingredients%20like%3Cem%3E%C2%A0pholga%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eor%C2%A0%3Cem%3Efogla%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(Cooling%20food)%3Cem%3E%2C%20ber%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(Rajasthani%20Plum)%3Cem%3E%2C%20ker%20shangri%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(Caper%20berry)%20are%20commonly%20consumed.%20Most%20of%20the%20Rajasthani%20food%20served%20around%20the%20country%20like%C2%A0%3Cem%3Elaal%20maas%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(Red%20Meat%20Curry)%3Cem%3E%2C%20daal%20bati%2C%20ker%20shangri%20ki%20sabzi%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(Caper%20berry%20curry)%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eall%20come%20from%20these%20regions.%20But%20what%20about%20the%20rest%20of%20it%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20Bagad%20region%20which%20comprises%20Hunumangarh%20and%20Ganganagar%2C%20is%20also%20known%20as%20the%20Punjab%20of%20Rajasthan%2C%20because%20of%20its%20lush%20and%20fertile%20lands.%20Their%20eating%20habits%20are%20very%20different%20from%20Marwar.%20The%20Chambal%20river%20flows%20in%20the%20Mewar%20region%2C%20and%20because%20of%20the%20availability%20of%20fresh%20water%2C%20they%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20dishes%20that%20include%20fish.%20But%20because%20it%20does%20not%20fit%20into%20the%20homogenous%20idea%20of%20Rajasthan%2C%20all%20this%20is%20often%20excluded.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20her%20curated%20dining%20experiences%20and%20pop-up%20events%2C%20Dipali%20brings%20out%20these%20underrated%20aspects%20of%20Rajasthani%20cuisine.%20She%20introduces%20these%20dishes%20to%20a%20wider%20audience%20and%20helps%20them%20develop%20a%20deeper%20connection%20to%20the%20food%20they%E2%80%99re%20enjoying%20by%20giving%20them%20a%20thorough%20understanding%20of%20its%20origins%20and%20cultural%20significance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EEncouraging%20children%20to%20document%20their%20family%20recipes%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20core%20principles%20of%20%E2%80%98The%20Kindness%20Meal%E2%80%99%20is%20generational%20sharing%2C%20where%20older%20generations%20pass%20down%20their%20knowledge%20of%20food%20and%20recipes%20to%20younger%20people.%20This%20is%20crucial%20in%20a%20time%20when%20traditional%20recipes%20are%20being%20lost%20due%20to%20the%20changing%20dynamics%20of%20family%20structures%20and%20lifestyles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20organise%20%E2%80%98Food%20Culture%20Play%20Dates%E2%80%99%20for%20children%20aged%20between%20seven%20and%2014%2C%20which%20aims%20to%20teach%20children%20about%20the%20importance%20of%20food%20in%20their%20cultural%20heritage.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20train%20the%20kids%20to%20be%20ethnographic%20and%20document%20their%20family%20recipes%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dipali%20explains.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20also%20creates%20this%20sense%20of%20wonder%20%E2%80%94%20what%20was%20the%20food%2C%20and%20where%20is%20it%20coming%20from%3F%20And%20makes%20you%20want%20to%20know%20more.%E2%80%9D%20The%20children%20are%20encouraged%20to%20speak%20to%20their%20family%20members%2